<subSubSection id="C36A8DB4FF80FFA6FCD0FCB6FDD00F49" lastPageId="38" lastPageNumber="483" pageId="37" pageNumber="482" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BCFDE3FFF80FFA5FCD0FCB6FBEB0909" blockId="37.[826,1442,778,1904]" pageId="37" pageNumber="482">
<emphasis id="B904022DFF80FFA5FCD0FCB6FC4C0D02" box="[826,927,778,799]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="482">Remarks</emphasis>
: 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE1A3CEFF80FFA5FC44FCB6FB340D3D" author="Chevaldonne P &amp; Olu K" box="[942,1255,778,800]" pageId="37" pageNumber="482" pagination="286 - 298" refId="ref63268" refString="Chevaldonne P, Olu K. 1996. Occurrence of anomuran crabs (Crustacea: Decapoda) in hydrothermal vent and cold-seep communities: a review. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington 109 (2): 286 - 298." type="journal article" year="1996">Chevaldonné &amp; Olu (1996)</bibRefCitation>
, in their review of anomurans from vents and seeps and citing 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE1A3CEFF80FFA5FA8AFC95FC6C0D40" author="Suess E &amp; Carson B &amp; Ritger SD &amp; Moore JC &amp; Jones ML &amp; Kulm LD &amp; Cochrane GR" pageId="37" pageNumber="482" pagination="475 - 484" refId="ref77539" refString="Suess E, Carson B, Ritger SD, Moore JC, Jones ML, Kulm LD, Cochrane GR. 1985. Biological communities at vent sites along the subduction zone off Oregon. Bulletin of the Biological Society of Washington 6: 475 - 484." type="journal article" year="1985">
Suess 
<emphasis id="B904022DFF80FFA5FCD0FCF4FCA10D41" box="[826,882,839,861]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="482">et al.</emphasis>
(1985)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE1A3CEFF80FFA5FC1CFCFBFB100D40" author="Kulm LD &amp; Suess E &amp; Moore JC &amp; Carson B &amp; Lewis BT &amp; Ritger SD &amp; Kadko DC &amp; Thornburg TM &amp; Embley RW &amp; Rugh WD &amp; Massoth GJ &amp; Langseth MG &amp; Cochrane GR &amp; Scamman RL" box="[1014,1219,839,861]" pageId="37" pageNumber="482" pagination="561 - 566" refId="ref69850" refString="Kulm LD, Suess E, Moore JC, Carson B, Lewis BT, Ritger SD, Kadko DC, Thornburg TM, Embley RW, Rugh WD, Massoth GJ, Langseth MG, Cochrane GR, Scamman RL. 1986. Oregon subduction zone: venting, fauna, and carbonates. Science 231: 561 - 566." type="journal article" year="1986">
Kulm 
<emphasis id="B904022DFF80FFA5FBD6FCF4FBA70D41" box="[1084,1140,839,861]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="482">et al.</emphasis>
(1986)
</bibRefCitation>
, noted that the first record of any lithodid from such habitats was an illustration of what was clearly a lithodid in a sketch of the cold-seep community along the lower Oregonian Subduction Zone (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE1A3CEFF80FFA5FC36FC7EFB770DC5" author="Suess E &amp; Carson B &amp; Ritger SD &amp; Moore JC &amp; Jones ML &amp; Kulm LD &amp; Cochrane GR" box="[988,1188,962,984]" pageId="37" pageNumber="482" pagination="475 - 484" refId="ref77539" refString="Suess E, Carson B, Ritger SD, Moore JC, Jones ML, Kulm LD, Cochrane GR. 1985. Biological communities at vent sites along the subduction zone off Oregon. Bulletin of the Biological Society of Washington 6: 475 - 484." type="journal article" year="1985">
Suess 
<emphasis id="B904022DFF80FFA5FBCFFC7FFB8E0DCA" box="[1061,1117,962,984]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="482">et al.</emphasis>
, 1985
</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 1; see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE1A3CEFF80FFA5FAF6FC7EFCA00DEA" author="Kulm LD &amp; Suess E &amp; Moore JC &amp; Carson B &amp; Lewis BT &amp; Ritger SD &amp; Kadko DC &amp; Thornburg TM &amp; Embley RW &amp; Rugh WD &amp; Massoth GJ &amp; Langseth MG &amp; Cochrane GR &amp; Scamman RL" pageId="37" pageNumber="482" pagination="561 - 566" refId="ref69850" refString="Kulm LD, Suess E, Moore JC, Carson B, Lewis BT, Ritger SD, Kadko DC, Thornburg TM, Embley RW, Rugh WD, Massoth GJ, Langseth MG, Cochrane GR, Scamman RL. 1986. Oregon subduction zone: venting, fauna, and carbonates. Science 231: 561 - 566." type="journal article" year="1986">
Kulm 
<emphasis id="B904022DFF80FFA5FA89FC7FFA470DCA" box="[1379,1428,962,984]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="482">et al</emphasis>
., 1986
</bibRefCitation>
, for map). From this same area but at slightly shallower depths, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE1A3CEFF80FFA5FBFEFC43FB220A08" author="Carey AG Jr &amp; Stein DL &amp; Taghon GL &amp; DeBevoise AE" box="[1044,1265,1023,1045]" pageId="37" pageNumber="482" pagination="137 - 149" refId="ref62363" refString="Carey AG Jr, Stein DL, Taghon GL, DeBevoise AE. 1988. Biology and ecology of the Oregon continental shelf edge associated with the accretionary prism. In: De Luca MP, Babb I, eds. Global venting, midwater, and benthic ecological processes. Groton: NOAA, 137 - 149." type="book chapter" year="1988">
Carey 
<emphasis id="B904022DFF80FFA5FB8FFBBCFB4E0A09" box="[1125,1181,1023,1045]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="482">et al.</emphasis>
(1988)
</bibRefCitation>
later reported 
<taxonomicName id="4C70A5BCFF80FFA5FCD0FBA2FBBD0A2E" box="[826,1134,1054,1075]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lithodidae" genus="Lopholithodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="37" pageNumber="482" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="foraminatus">
<emphasis id="B904022DFF80FFA5FCD0FBA2FBBD0A2E" box="[826,1134,1054,1075]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="482">Lopholithodes foraminatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but it is not known if the earlier observations were of this same species. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE1A3CEFF80FFA5FABEFB81FBEB0A6C" author="Tunnicliffe V &amp; Jensen RG" pageId="37" pageNumber="482" pagination="2443 - 2449" refId="ref78380" refString="Tunnicliffe V, Jensen RG. 1987. Distribution and behavior of the spider crab Macroregonia macrochira Sakai (Brachyura) around the hydrothermal vents of the northeast Pacific. Canadian Journal of Zoology 65: 2443 - 2449." type="journal article" year="1987">Tunnicliffe &amp; Jensen (1987)</bibRefCitation>
noted that the earlier illustration might have been based on a species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C70A5BCFF80FFA5FAC4FBC6FA710A92" authorityName="WHITE" authorityYear="1856" box="[1326,1442,1146,1167]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lithodidae" genus="Paralomis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="37" pageNumber="482" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B904022DFF80FFA5FAC4FBC6FA710A92" box="[1326,1442,1146,1167]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="482">Paralomis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
found by them at vents in the Juan de Fuca Ridge system (see below). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE1A3CEFF80FFA5FC1DFB0BFAFB0AD0" author="Chevaldonne P &amp; Olu K" box="[1015,1320,1207,1229]" pageId="37" pageNumber="482" pagination="286 - 298" refId="ref63268" refString="Chevaldonne P, Olu K. 1996. Occurrence of anomuran crabs (Crustacea: Decapoda) in hydrothermal vent and cold-seep communities: a review. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington 109 (2): 286 - 298." type="journal article" year="1996">Chevaldonné &amp; Olu (1996)</bibRefCitation>
listed ‘two species and six occurrences not yet clearly assigned to species’. The situation has not changed appreciably since then (see below), and the review by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE1A3CEFF80FFA5FAE7FAAFFC0E0B55" author="Chevaldonne P &amp; Olu K" pageId="37" pageNumber="482" pagination="286 - 298" refId="ref63268" refString="Chevaldonne P, Olu K. 1996. Occurrence of anomuran crabs (Crustacea: Decapoda) in hydrothermal vent and cold-seep communities: a review. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington 109 (2): 286 - 298." type="journal article" year="1996">Chevaldonné &amp; Olu (1996)</bibRefCitation>
remains a well-written and succinct introduction to the literature on vent- and seep-associated lithodids. According to those authors, cold-seep lithodids are known from 
<quantity id="4C8873DAFF80FFA5FB8CFA32FAD80BB9" box="[1126,1291,1422,1444]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1435" metricValueMax="2.037" metricValueMin="0.25" pageId="37" pageNumber="482" unit="m" value="1143.5" valueMax="2037.0" valueMin="250.0">250 to 2037 m</quantity>
depths, with one personal observation (M. Sibuet) of a depth of 
<quantity id="4C8873DAFF80FFA5FCD0FA70FC5D0BFC" box="[826,910,1484,1505]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.8" pageId="37" pageNumber="482" unit="m" value="3800.0">3800 m</quantity>
in the Nankai Trough of the 
<collectingCountry id="F3679EAFFF80FFA5FB32FA70FACD0BFC" box="[1240,1310,1484,1505]" name="Japan" pageId="37" pageNumber="482">Japan</collectingCountry>
subduction zone, whereas hydrothermal vent-associated lithodids are known from 
<quantity id="4C8873DAFF80FFA5FBEEF9B5FB420803" box="[1028,1169,1545,1567]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.175" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="0.35" pageId="37" pageNumber="482" unit="m" value="1175.0" valueMax="2000.0" valueMin="350.0">350–2000 m</quantity>
. Many reports exist of unidentified lithodids at vent or seep sites (in some cases, such as the paper by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE1A3CEFF80FFA5FB7AF9FAFABE0846" author="Sassen R &amp; Brooks JM &amp; MacDonal IR &amp; Kennicutt MC II &amp; Guinasso NL Jr &amp; Requejo AG" box="[1168,1389,1606,1628]" pageId="37" pageNumber="482" pagination="349 - 355" refId="ref76247" refString="Sassen R, Brooks JM, MacDonal IR, Kennicutt MC II, Guinasso NL Jr, Requejo AG. 1993. Association of oil seeps and chemosynthetic communities with oil discoveries, upper continental slope, Gulf of Mexico. Transactions of the Gulf Coast Association of Geological Societies 43: 349 - 355." type="journal article" year="1993">
Sassen 
<emphasis id="B904022DFF80FFA5FB01F9FBFAF00846" box="[1259,1315,1606,1628]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="482">et al.</emphasis>
, 1993
</bibRefCitation>
, the species was later identified). Interestingly, despite their wide depth and geographical range, lithodids have not been reported from any of the EPR, Galapagos Rift (with the possible exception of a report by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE1A3CEFF80FFA5FCD0F963FB5308EB" author="Guinot D &amp; Macpherson E" box="[826,1152,1759,1782]" pageId="37" pageNumber="482" pagination="111 - 114" refId="ref66817" refString="Guinot D, Macpherson E. 1987. Une araignee de mer qui n' En est pas une. L'Univers du Vivant 24: 111 - 114." type="journal article" year="1987">Guinot &amp; Macpherson, 1987</bibRefCitation>
) or MAR systems (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE1A3CEFF80FFA5FAB4F963FBFE0909" author="Chevaldonne P &amp; Olu K" pageId="37" pageNumber="482" pagination="286 - 298" refId="ref63268" refString="Chevaldonne P, Olu K. 1996. Occurrence of anomuran crabs (Crustacea: Decapoda) in hydrothermal vent and cold-seep communities: a review. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington 109 (2): 286 - 298." type="journal article" year="1996">Chevaldonné &amp; Olu, 1996</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCFDE3FFF80FFA6FCB9F8A1FDD00F49" blockId="37.[826,1442,778,1904]" lastBlockId="38.[142,758,195,340]" lastPageId="38" lastPageNumber="483" pageId="37" pageNumber="482">
Species belonging to this large and widespread family are assumed to be vagrants as opposed to vent- or seep-endemics, even though some are known only from such sites (see below and also 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE1A3CEFF83FFA6FDABFF7FFEDF0EE5" author="Chevaldonne P &amp; Olu K" pageId="38" pageNumber="483" pagination="286 - 298" refId="ref63268" refString="Chevaldonne P, Olu K. 1996. Occurrence of anomuran crabs (Crustacea: Decapoda) in hydrothermal vent and cold-seep communities: a review. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington 109 (2): 286 - 298." type="journal article" year="1996">Chevaldonné &amp; Olu (1996)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE1A3CEFF83FFA6FEF0FF5EFE240EE5" author="Macpherson E" box="[282,503,226,248]" pageId="38" pageNumber="483" pagination="9 - 153" refId="ref70868" refString="Macpherson E. 1988. Revision of the family Lithodidae Samouelle, 1819 (Crustacea, Decapoda, Anomura) in the Atlantic Ocean. Monografias de Zoologia Marina 2: 9 - 153." type="journal article" year="1988">Macpherson (1988)</bibRefCitation>
provided an in-depth revision and review of all known Atlantic species of this family; see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE1A3CEFF83FFA6FED4FEA3FDC40F28" author="Macpherson E" box="[318,535,287,309]" pageId="38" pageNumber="483" pagination="797 - 805" refId="ref71076" refString="Macpherson E. 2001. New species and new records of lithodid crabs (Crustacea, Decapoda) from the southwestern and central Pacific. Zoosystema 23 (4): 797 - 805." type="journal article" year="2001">Macpherson (2001)</bibRefCitation>
for a brief overview of the family in the Indo-Pacific.
</paragraph>
